content: Owncloud on Android isn't bad, but could be better. I have a self-hosted OwnCloud server and so far (about a hour) I love it! I am able to log in on the web app, upload and download files, and do everything I'd expect. The Android app was able to connect and see my files with no issue. I was also able to upload, download, and delete files and all changes were shown immediately. My only complaint is with synching. There isn't a way to auto sync old files. The file sync or backup works for anything added since I installed the app on my phone, but old files were not automatically backed up. I think many would appreciate the ability to do incremental backups to sync any files that were changed or are yet to be uploaded from the monitored folder. I only care because this is a paid app and (so far) this is my only gripe. Adding a way to sync existing files would make my life complete.

content: The app works fine as far as connecting to my ownCloud is concerned, however... I particularly liked the option of automatically backing up my photos from my phone to my server. I thought that I would set it up to back up over WiFi and when I connect to WiFi, the app will automatically upload all new pics to the server. It can't be further from the truth. The app does not do anything automatically. When I'm not on the WiFi when the pic is taken, it hangs in the queue and is not uploaded when I connect. When I start the queue manually, the app crashes randomly, so some pics get uploaded, others not. It is extremely buggy and does not serve the purpose of fully automatic backup that I do not have to take care about. Pitty.
replyContent:
Hi, to solve the auto upload issues for everyone, we need more information. Can you please send the following information to apps@owncloud.com:
- Device name
- Android version
- ownCloud app version
- energy saving settings
- can you think of other useful information?

thanks a lot! ^el

We highly recommend upgrading your server to version 10. Running an outdated server is a security risk and not supported.

content: I would have liked to use this app. I really could use access to my file server on my Android. Unfortunately, for me, I can't access my server via this app. The reason for this is because I run both server side SSL and client side SSL. The certificate in question is imported to my device and accessible to apps according to permissions and I can access my files via the browser on my device.   As of yet, this application has not elected to implement such security protocols as far as I can find. This is regretful. I cannot comment on any other aspects of this app at all. This is just a statement that anyone using two-factor SSL authentication in the form of client certs - you cannot use this app. I hope that this will be implemented before long.
replyContent: Thank you very much for your valuable feedback. We are working on it. You can track the progress here: https://github.com/owncloud/android/issues/163#issuecomment-320507513 ^el

replyContent: Hi, this is a known limitation of self-signed SSL certificates. The Android client can't stream with self signed SSL-certificates. You should get a lets encrypt certificate, it's more secure, too! https://letsencrypt.org/ ^el

It even plays music within the app without having to open a media player (not always a plus: it does only one song at a time). I wish it were easier to switch between accounts but it's not that bad. I like how it can back up my photos to my server without having to go through Google. Especially useful for work photos that I don't want to share with a third party.

Most likely a killer app which deserves a prize, but... wasn't expecting that I needed my own private webhosting account. Not what I was looking for. Not interested in an app which needs so much configuration, too much configuration takes out the productivity. So as much as I would like to give this app a full house of stars because it's probably just awesome, I give it only 3 due to the info wasn't clear enough to me about how this app functions and then that it needs your own webhosting, which is probably great, but not that great for me. Perhaps others think it's great, but that doesn't apply to me. So, I'm sorry for my "bad" review and actually would like a refund although I think your app is awesome, just not awesome for me.

content: I am sure this will have much more functionality before long so worth the 63p, 1 dollar in my opinion to support development.

There is great potential for this app, but it lacks some standard features that one has come to expect from similar apps such as Dropbox. At this point I find that two missing features in particular stand out: (1) no thumbnail view of images and (2) no ability to send links to files. Other useful additions to the app would be the ability to select multiple files, an integrated way to sync contacts and calendar, and the ability to choose where the files will be stored (external SD card rather than phone memory would be nice). I consider my purchase a donation to a good cause and hope to see improvements through user support.

Installation and connecting to my own owncloud was quick and painless.  However the client is severely lacking in some basic features: 1) No way (?) to sync the entire contents of your owncloud - have to sync each file/folder individually.  This may be a good thing as it allows you to only sync the items you actually want on your phone, however it would be equally good to be able to say "sync all" and then unselect certain items. 2) No way to specify the location on your phone. This is a BIG problem for people whose main memory is more or less full but have an SD card available. 3) No way to specify the auto-upload location of photos. 4) No way to share files/folders with other users  While owncloud itself is great I struggle to be able to recommend this client in its current state as a paid-for app. Once fully-featured, I'd be more than happy to recommend it.

content: This was working and now it updated. Force closes always. Bad Form cloud crew Bad Form
Works nicely on my SG note.
Latest version doesn't loop or crash anymore, but never syncs local changes back to server. They get overwritten instead. So it's a download-only client right now.

(0) The pictures that are newly uploaded are corrupted? My computer is not able to read the recently uploaded. (1) Fails very frequently to upload pictures. No chance to retry? How do I see the list of failed upload other than the notification bar? Clicking on fail notification should lead to the file that failed to give  a chance to retry, and to know the reason. How about a red X on the files that failed when browsing? (2) Nice additions: select all, video/picture thumbnail view, todo list sync. (3) For the OwnCloud server, Google Calendar/Contact sync, not just mounting GDrive.
Yes, it's low cost but maybe a trial period for evaluation would be better. Will come back and update my review once i've had chance to test. Struggles with multiple uploads.
Works fine but very basic compared to others eg drop box.
File syncing is enough for me, other "app" clutter would likely be annoying.

Works good but would be nice to be able to select multiple files and directories for syncing. Tried to upload several directorys w/ pix inside; After the upload, all directorys were stripped off and all the pix ended up in one directory on the server. Aside from that, its works pretty good from what I can see. Have just had it installed for two days now.
Does not sync changes made to files on phone back to the server.
The best ive found anywhere! You guys are the best! I recently got a new phone and once i installed this app everything from my old phone appeared on my new phone. Im a happy camper..

content: I always tried to use the free app in the past but that one didn't work at all. So I was really excited and finally bought the "commercial" version. But disappointment followed quickly after my purchase: Already when trying to enter the URL and the credentials I got stuck as the "Connect" button remains disabled whatever I enter in the form fields. Pretty annoying I have to say

I should have listened to the other reviews. This thing is not even beta quality and the slow pace of its development indicates it may never get there.   Odd error messages, random crashes and a serious lack of features cripple what could be a dropbox killer.
Loses my account details every time the phone restarts.
Can only download certain mime types, thinks epub files are folders and can't download them, other types of files aren't even listed in the folder view.
Nice and simple.  I have no problem paying for this since Owncloud server was free.  Keep up the good work Owncloud developers.
I guess I should have just kept the original one by Bartek Przybylski? This one keeps loosing my account info on JB 4.1.1 ... continued development would be nice though.
It lacks even logout button. Currently unusable but promising.

I'm really a fan of OwnCloud. I installed an instance on my linux server at home an sync several windows PCs. But without an automatic synchronization of files modified on my android device, this app is absolutely useless for me. I hope you guys will implement this feature ASAP. I will check GitHub. Perhaps I can do it on my own.
It should include contacts and calendar sync, its more important than synchronising files on mobile phone.

I agree with earlier posts, it should not be out of alpha release: why should I pay for this? Downloading multiple files crashes app/phone, keeping files up-to-date crashes app/phone.  You can download single files and upload single files. This app has less functionality than the web GUI. Quit charging people for your broken trash.

Any network failure to connect to an own cloud server and it forgets the account which stops instant upload as well. Not the best programming decision. I shouldn't have to continuously be reading my server info.

After spending an age trying set this up on my server, failing, and then opting to pay  for a hosted install I'm actually very happy with this. Not quite sure how reliable at backup this is just yet but so far so good

Can't believe I paid money for this. Biggest bug bear is that it loses account credentials on reboot, and I do that a lot considering I'm using cm10 roms. And it's been like this for a while. No acknowledgement or a fix. Use, and but only if you never reboot, then else it'll just get too painful.
Modifying a "keep sync" file causes infinite upload loop to the server. Unusable in my opinion. Maybe in the future
Getting better

Accepts any certificate without complaint. Currently too insecure to use on public wifi. Thankfully openvpn works well, making it possible to securely run own cloud for now. Desperately needs certificate pinning!

Not prefect but seems to be getting better all the time. Have disabled the instant picture upload because it didn't work very well but find the ability to access my files anywhere really good. Thanks and keep up the good work.

EDIT: The latest version seems to fix battery drain issues.  I won't knock this app too much since this is the very first release, but it goes without saying that there are a lot of changes that need to be made. Why am I unable to select multiple items? Why can't I download a folder? Why am I unable to press a button to get a share link in the file context menu? I could do that on the Tonido app, and I really miss it.  On the plus side, instant upload seems really nifty.
Sync was intermittent at best,  and for the last 24 hours hasn't updated at all
Nice idea, nice app. Please keep going! Would be good to have sync status or log info,like in desktop sync client.
